Images in HTML: 

Basic Image Syntax:
<img src="path-to-image.jpg" alt="Description of image">

--src = source of the image (URL or file path)
--alt = alternative text (shown if image can't load; good for accessibility)

Example with Local Image:
<img src="images/dog.jpg" alt="Cute Dog" width="300" height="200">
--width and height control image size (in pixels)

Example with Online Image:
<img src="https://www.w3schools.com/images/lamp.jpg" alt="Lamp Image">

Example Code:

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>HTML Images</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Day 8: Adding Images in HTML</h1>

    <h2>Local Image</h2>
    <img src="images/sample.jpg" alt="Sample Local Image" width="300" height="200">

    <h2>Online Image</h2>
    <img src="https://

